<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  WarOfTheLionsJobCommandData.xml

  IMPORTANT 1: Only include entries/properties you've actually changed - this gets merged with
  every other mod's changes to this table, cell by cell. Don't paste this whole file into your
  own mod unmodified.
  IMPORTANT 2: Id must be 224, 225, or 226 (0xE0-0xE2). This is a 3-entry extension of
  JobCommandData, not a standalone table - see FFTOWarOfTheLionsJobCommandDataManager for why.
  UPDATE: ability/RSM ids below are now filled in, decoded from the classic PSP SkillSetsBin.bin
  (including the per-slot "add 256" extend-id flag bits stored in each entry's first 3 bytes -
  missed in an earlier draft of this file, which is why some ids here differ from that draft's
  comments, e.g. Darkness's 5th action is really 357/Unholy Sacrifice, not 101/Pummel).
  Verified two ways: (1) re-decoded straight from the binary, byte for byte, matches exactly;
  (2) cross-checked against FFTGenericJobs' own shipped Ability-en - it already restores real
  names+effects for Dark Knight's core abilities (184/219/220/357, 484/485), confirming these
  aren't just correct classic ids but genuinely live, working abilities today. Piracy's Plunder
  family (358-366) is the exception - still unused everywhere checked, vanilla and
  FFTGenericJobs both, since Sky Pirate was never part of that mod's scope. Fixed one bug from
  the original submission: ExtendAbilityIdFlagBits was left at 0 on 224 and 225 despite both
  having action values over 255, which would silently truncate to the wrong ability when written
  (e.g. 357 -> 101) without the matching Extended flag set.

  Refer to: https://ffhacktics.com/wiki/Skillsets (classic PSP skillset reference)
-->
